			<div type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn" rendition="class:83225 maturity:83211"><!--
Comments below by Csaba Kiss and Dániel Balogh (BD) are offered "as is" and do not represent a thoroughly researched or considered opinion.
--><!--
Lal, H., 'Sarangarh copper plates of Maha-Sudeva',
Epigraphia Indica vol IX, pp. 281-285
--><p><pb

n="1v"/><lb
n="1"/><g type="mangala"/>
svasti<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied>
śarabha-purād vikkramopanata-sāmanta-makuṭa-cūḍā-maṇi-prabhā-pra<lb
n="2" break="no"/>sekāmbu-dhauta-pāda-yugalo<!--
L2. Lal reads dhota, emending to dhauta. His editor observes that the vowel mark is different from that for o and may actually be meant for au (here and in other plates of this ruler). I (D. Balogh) concur wholeheartedly, the mark is conspicuously distinct from o, e.g. in l1 and l2.
-->ripu-vilāsinī-sīmantoddharaṇa-hetur vvasu-
<lb
n="3"/>vasudhā-go-pradaḫ parama-bhāgavato
mātā-pit<choice><sic>ri</sic><corr>r̥</corr></choice>-pādānuddhyātaś śrī-mahā-sude<lb
n="4" break="no"/>va-rājaḥ tuṇḍaraka-bhuktīya-cullaṇḍarake prativāsi-kuṭumbinas sa<lb
n="5" break="no"/>mājñāpayati</p>
<p>viditam astu vo yathāyaṁ grāmaḥ tridaśapati-sadana-sukha-
<lb
n="6"/>pratiṣṭhā-karo yāvad ravi-śaśi-tārā-kiraṇa-pratihata-ghorāndhakāraṁ ja<pb

n="2r" break="no"/><lb
n="7" break="no"/>gad avatiṣṭhate tāvad upabhogyas sanidhis sopanidhir acāṭa-bhaṭa-prāveśya-
<lb
n="8"/>sarvva-kara-visarjjitaḥ rājya-mahādevī-r<choice><sic>o</sic><corr>ā</corr></choice>ja-kulaiḥ mātā-pitror ātmana<surplus>ṁ</surplus>ś ca pu<lb
n="9" break="no"/>ṇyābhivr̥ddhaye Udaka-pūrvvaṁ
kauśika-sagotra-tri-sahasra-vidya-bhāskarasvāmi-
<lb
n="10"/>prabhākarasvāmi-barbbarisvāmi-botasvāmi-dattasvāmi-viṣṇusvāmi-
<lb
n="11"/>phalgusvāmi-svāmikīrttisvāmi-śaṅkarasvāminā<supplied reason="omitted">m</supplied>
tām<surplus>b</surplus>ra-śāsanenātisr̥<lb
n="12" break="no"/>ṣṭo bhūtvāsmābhir anumoditaḥ</p>
<p>te yūyam evam upalabhyaiṣām ājñā-śrava<pb

n="2v" break="no"/><lb
n="13" break="no"/>ṇa-vidheyā bhūtvā yathocitaṁ bhoga-bhāgam upanayantas sukha<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied> prativatsyatha<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied>
<lb
n="14"/>bhaviṣyataś ca bhūmipān anudarśayati||
</p>
<lg n="1" met="vasantatilakā">
<l n="a">dānād viśiṣṭam anupālana-ja<supplied reason="omitted">ṁ</supplied> pu<lb
n="15" break="no"/>rāṇā<surplus>ṁḥ</surplus></l>
<l n="b">dharmmeṣu niścita-dhiyaḫ pravadanti dharmmaM||</l>


<l n="c">tasmā<supplied reason="omitted">d</supplied> dvijāya su-vi<lb
n="16" break="no"/>śuddha-kula-śrutāya</l>
<l n="d">dattāṁ bhuvaṁ bhavatu vo matir eva goptuṁ||</l>
</lg>
<p>tad bhavadbhi<lb
n="17" break="no"/>r apy eṣā dattir anupālayitavyā<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied>
vyāsa-gītāṁś cātra ślokān udāhara<lb
n="18" break="no"/>nti||
</p>
<lg n="2" met="indravajrā"><!--
Garuḍapurāṇa 2.42.4
-->
<l n="a">agner apatyaṁ prathamaṁ suvarṇṇaṁ</l>
<l n="b">bhūr vvaiṣṇavī sūryya-sutā<supplied reason="omitted">ś ca gāvaḥ</supplied></l>


<l n="c"><supplied reason="omitted">dattās trayas tena bhavanti lokā</supplied></l>
<l n="d"><supplied reason="omitted">yaḥ kāñcanaṁ gāñ ca mahīñ ca dadyāt</supplied></l>
</lg>
